## 📌 Project Overview

This project focuses on analyzing an FMCG (Fast-Moving Consumer Goods) revenue dataset to uncover key business insights related to **sales performance, profitability, and regional trends**.

Using SQL, the dataset was cleaned, transformed, and analyzed to extract meaningful insights that can support **data-driven business decisions**.

---

## 🎯 Objective

> Transform raw FMCG sales data into actionable insights to improve revenue, profitability, and business strategy.

---

## 🗂️ Dataset Description

The dataset includes the following key fields:

- 📅 Date  
- 🌍 Region / Country  
- 🏷️ Brand / Product  
- 📦 Category  
- 🔢 Units Sold  
- 💰 Revenue  
- 💸 Cost  
- 📈 Profit  

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies

- **SQL** → Data extraction & analysis  

---

## 🔍 Key Analysis Performed

- Revenue and profit analysis by region, product, and brand  
- Month-over-Month (MoM) and Year-over-Year (YoY) growth trends  
- Profit margin and cost analysis  
- Top and bottom-performing products  
- Regional performance comparison  
- Pareto analysis (Top 20% products contribution)

---

## 📊 Key Insights

- 📉 Some regions generate **high revenue but low profit margins**  
- 🏆 A small percentage of products contribute to the **majority of revenue**  
- 📆 Strong **seasonal trends** observed in sales  
- 💸 High operational costs impacting profitability in certain regions  

---

## 🚀 Business Recommendations

- Optimize supply chain to reduce operational costs  
- Improve pricing strategies for low-margin products  
- Focus marketing efforts on high-performing products  
- Increase inventory planning during peak seasons  

---

## 🧠 SQL Concepts Used

- Joins (INNER, LEFT)  
- Group By & Aggregations  
- Window Functions (RANK, ROW_NUMBER, SUM OVER)  
- Subqueries & CTEs  
- Case Statements  

